            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 2</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgBingZhao0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgBingZhao0', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Longquan kiln complex, diameter: 35.2 cm, late 14th to early 15th century, from the Vohemar site, Madagascar (Musée d’Histoire naturelle de Nîmes). All rights reserved to Dr. Bing Zhou, who has kindly permitted the use of these photographs for educational purposes. (<htcite0>)</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Families: Great Zimbabwe - civilization built by the Shona people, one of the Bantu-speaking groups, in Zimbabwe. (<htcite1>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 2</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgBZ0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgBZ0', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Jingdezhen kiln complex and southern China (Zhongguo 中國), 11th to early 13th century, proven from the Sanje ya Kati site, Kilwa-Masoko, Tanzania. All rights reserved to Dr. Bing Zhou, who has kindly permitted the use of these photographs for educational purposes. (<htcite0>)</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Families: Great Zimbabwe - civilization built by the Shona people, one of the Bantu-speaking groups, in Zimbabwe. (<htcite1>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
